oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Allen Holladay, Conservation Aide, SCS and Clyde Johnson, farmer, examine pulpwood cut from a 26 year old loblolly pine plantation planted by the C.C.C. (Civilian Conservation Corps) in 1939 for control of erosion. Located in Carroll County, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The C.C.C. (Civilian Conservation Corps) was a federal work relief program established in 1933 under the administration of Pres. Franklin D. Roosevelt.
